# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Git LFS routing for generated / large media (#294, step 2.1 "Corrigir novos commits")
#
# DESIGN (strict, fail-closed):
#   - Large media is ONLY exempt from the size gate when committed INSIDE the
#     designated LFS staging area `assets/_lfs/`. There is deliberately NO global
#     filter=lfs rule for audio/video/archive suffixes: a stray media file at repo
#     root is treated as a raw, pack-inflating blob and BLOCKED by
#     scripts/repository_budget.py (rule 2), forcing it into assets/_lfs/ or into
#     GitHub Releases / artifact storage.
#   - The ephemeral output prefixes (video/out/, rust/target/, node_modules/, dist/,
#     build/) are FORBIDDEN entirely by the gate (rule 1) — never committed, raw or
#     LFS. They are reproduced by build tooling or fetched from Releases.
#
# None of these patterns match a CURRENTLY tracked file (verified: git ls-files shows
# no .mp4/.zip/etc. and no video/out/ blobs), so enabling LFS here rewrites no existing
# object — it only governs FUTURE commits. The grandfathered hero images in
# assets/*.png stay ordinary git blobs on purpose (moving them to LFS needs a history
# rewrite, which #294's Definition of Done gates behind a separate approved step; they
# are size-grandfathered in scripts/repository_budget_baseline.json instead).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Designated LFS staging area — media committed here is stored in LFS (a small pointer
# in git), so it does NOT inflate the pack. The budget gate recognizes this prefix as
# exempt (AC "asset LFS permitido passa"). Put generated demo video/audio/zip here, or
# publish them via GitHub Releases / release artifacts and keep only small sources in git.
assets/_lfs/**  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Line-ending normalization for source; keep binary assets binary so git never mangles
# them and never stores a re-encoded (size-changing) copy in the pack.
*       text=auto eol=lf
*.png   binary
*.webp  binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
